items.badge_description: There's beer in them thar hills! You're setting off on your journey through the world of beer, but be sure to take a little time to get to know each brewery as you go. That's a beer from 170 different breweries. Try 5 more for Level 35!

items.badge_name: Beyond a Shadow of a Stout (Level 6)
items.badge_description: We all love Stouts, and now we have a dedicated badge to celebrate your dedication to these dark, top-fermented beer in multiple variations, like Oatmeal, Milk and more! Which one will you start with? That's 30 different beers with the style of Stout. Try 5 more for Level 7!

Porters and Stouts are rich with both history and flavor. Roasty, dark, and delicious, these two styles helped start it all. That’s 345 different beers with the style of Porter or Stout. Try 5 more for Level 70!
It takes the perfect amount of light, the right framing and a touch of creative love to get the perfect picture of your brew. Now it’s time to drink it! That’s 180 check-ins with a photo.

Porters and Stouts are rich with both history and flavor. Roasty, dark, and delicious, these two styles helped start it all. That’s 10 different beers with the style of Porter or Stout. Try 5 more for Level 3!

Looking for more kick than a session beer, but want to be able to stay for a few rounds? You have to keep it in the middle. That's 370 beers with an ABV greater than 5% and less than 10%.  Try 5 more for Level 75!

Fresh from the tap is one of the best ways to enjoy a beer. Just try to use a glass and not drink directly from the tap, as tempting as it may be. That's 205 checkins with the serving style of Draft. Try 5 more for Level 42!
Happy Untappd anniversary to you! Thanks for sticking around and drinking socially with us. Cheers! That's 1 year on Untappd!
Your quest to quench your thirst leaves no stone unturned! That's at least 30 distinct venues!

Looking for more kick than a session beer, but want to be able to stay for a few rounds? You have to keep it in the middle. That's 25 beers with an ABV greater than 5% and less than 10%. Try 5 more for Level 6!

It takes the perfect amount of light, the right framing and a touch of creative love to get the perfect picture of your brew. Now it’s time to drink it! That’s 50 check-ins with a photo. Take 5 more for Level 11!
Traveling the world is hard, but not for you. It's as easy as cracking open a new brew! You have had a beer from at least 5 different regions around the world. Try 5 more for Level 2!

Want to enjoy a day of brews, but need to keep your wits sharp? There are plenty of delicious brews under 5% for you to sip on throughout the day. That's 165 different beers with an ABV of 5% and lower. Try 5 more for Level 34!
Traveling the world is hard, but not for you. It's as easy as cracking open a new brew! You have had a beer from at least 110 different regions around the world. Try 5 more for Level 23!

beer.beer_description: In 1792 Richard Beamish & Richard Crawford, two Cork merchants, established the famous Beamish & Crawford brewery, situated in the heart of Cork city. To this day Beamish stout is being enjoyed in bars and homes throughout Ireland. Beamish has a rich roasted flavour with coffee and dark chocolate undertones, making it a genuine Irish stout.
Smoother, creamier. Unexpectedly refreshing Irish stout.
Fresh, natural, balenced, dry, sweet, tart, crisp
Christmas stout with a hint of cinnamon
Brewed under license in Ireland by Hop House for the Royal Coachman pub in Waterdown Ontario Canada
